==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electronic
<hw>E`lec*tron"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Physics &
Chem.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to an electron or
electrons; <as>as, <ex>electronic</ex> energy</as>.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Using the methods or principles of
<er>electronics</er> as part of the working mechanism; -- of devices;
<as>as, <ex>electronic</ex> circuit; <ex>electronic</ex> devices;
<ex>electronic</ex> entertainment devices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Using computerized storage or transmission of
information; <as>as, <ex>electronic</ex> banking; <ex>electronic</ex>
mail; <ex>electronic</ex> fund transfer.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to electronics.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>electronic device</ent>⟦br⟧
